<p id="Par17" class="p">Glacier mass balance (B) can be calculated as:
 <disp-formula id="Equ2" class="disp-formula">
  <label class="label">2</label>
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <tex-math id="M5" class="tex-math">\documentclass[12pt]{minimal} \usepackage{amsmath} \usepackage{wasysym} \usepackage{amsfonts} \usepackage{amssymb} \usepackage{amsbsy} \usepackage{mathrsfs} \usepackage{upgreek} \setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt} \begin{document}$$B={C}_{a}-{Q}_{M}/{l}_{m}+{E}_{V}+{R}_{F}$$\end{document}</tex-math>
   <math id="M6" display="block" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">B</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">C</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">a</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">âˆ’</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">Q</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">M</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">/</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">l</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">m</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">E</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">V</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
    <mo class="mo">+</mo>
    <msub class="msub">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">R</mi>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mi class="mi">F</mi>
     </mrow>
    </msub>
   </math>
   <graphic xlink:href="41598_2017_14256_Article_Equ2.gif" position="anchor" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
  </alternatives>
 </disp-formula>where 
 <italic class="italic">C</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">a</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">M</italic>
 </sub>/
 <italic class="italic">l</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">m</italic>
 </sub>, 
 <italic class="italic">E</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">V</italic>
 </sub>, and 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">F</italic>
 </sub> are accumulation, melt water, evaporation, and refreezing, respectively. 
 <italic class="italic">Q</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">M</italic>
 </sub>, and 
 <italic class="italic">l</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">m</italic>
 </sub> are heat for ice melt and latent heat for melting ice. 
 <italic class="italic">C</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">a</italic>
 </sub> is determined along with air temperature (snow or rain).
</p>
